        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 4:16PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Morrisville, or 9 miles south of Bolivar, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasant Hope, Morrisville, and Brighton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
